      "span_text": "Using the algorithms defined by Rein and Sirocko (2002) , three variables were extracted from the spectra: (1) the relative absorption band depth at 660-670 nm (RABD 660-670 ), which is a proxy for total sedimentary chlorin; (2) the ratio of reflectance at 660-670 nm (R 660 /R 670 ), which is a proxy for the degree of photopigment diagenesis; and (3) the ratio of reflectance at 590-640 nm (R 590 /R 640 ), which is a proxy for the lithogenic content, specifically illite, chlorite and mica [CITATION_1] )."
